Uh, I'm flying this plane today.
First complaint: We need cute flight logbooks. Black is too boring, and pink is actually salmon red, not pink at all.
I've wanted to fly since I was a kid.
Today my dream came true... I flew a plane today. I'm still in shock.
FlightAware data.
This Saturday I plan to try again. The weather doesn't look great right now, but today is only Monday.
It seems the challenges in this area are beginning to emerge. Due to the FAA's stance on certain medications, I may have difficulty obtaining a medical certificate.
This is not impossible, but it will take a lot of time and involve a lot of extra work.
Although this is a bit discouraging, it's just another problem to solve, and it seems "definitely" solvable at the moment. It just will require a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what challenges I will face next:
The FAA doesn't like ADHD. If you are taking medication for ADHD, you definitely won't get a medical certificate.
https://youtu.be/W5JSfq6LLAU?si=xIxPaY8ayqqNSj4c
If I ever have the opportunity to customize my plane's tail number, it has to be some variant of N1337_, where _ represents any available letter character.
Of course, the sun will rise as usual when I'm not around, haha. That's really spoiling the fun.
I need to get back into the air again. But this weather is really not cooperating.
Welcome to the world of general aviation! 😜
Based on the ads YouTube thinks I should see, the videos it recommends to me, and the comments, I feel that airlines tend to be conservative in their tracking.
